{
  "title": {
    "zh": "2026 数字资产管理趋势：从存储到智能协作",
    "en": "2026 DAM Trends: From Storage to Intelligent Collaboration"
  },
  "content": {
    "zh": {
      "root": {
        "type": "root",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "随着企业数字化转型的深入，数字资产管理（DAM）正经历从单纯的文件存储向智能协作平台的根本性转变。本文将探讨 2026 年最值得关注的五大趋势。" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "趋势一：AI 原生化" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "AI 不再是 DAM 系统的附加功能，而是成为核心架构的一部分。从自动分类、智能裁剪到内容生成，AI 贯穿资产管理的每一个环节。" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "趋势二：实时协作" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "远程办公常态化推动了 DAM 系统的协作能力升级。团队成员可以在同一资产上实时标注、评论和审批，消除了传统邮件往返的低效流程。" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "趋势三：跨平台无缝集成" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "现代 DAM 系统正在打破信息孤岛，与设计工具（Figma、Adobe）、项目管理（Notion、Linear）和营销平台（HubSpot）深度集成，形成完整的数字工作流。" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "展望" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "数字资产管理的未来属于那些能够将 AI 能力、协作体验和生态集成完美融合的平台。MuseDAM 正在这条道路上不断探索和创新。" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "version": 1
      }
    },
    "en": {
      "root": {
        "type": "root",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "As enterprises deepen their digital transformation, Digital Asset Management (DAM) is undergoing a fundamental shift from simple file storage to intelligent collaboration platforms. This article explores the five most important trends to watch in 2026." }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "Trend 1: AI-Native Architecture" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "AI is no longer an add-on feature for DAM systems — it has become a core part of the architecture. From automatic categorization and smart cropping to content generation, AI permeates every aspect of asset management." }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "Trend 2: Real-Time Collaboration" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "The normalization of remote work has driven collaboration capabilities in DAM systems to new heights. Team members can annotate, comment, and approve assets in real time, eliminating the inefficiency of traditional email-based workflows." }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "Trend 3: Seamless Cross-Platform Integration" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "Modern DAM systems are breaking down information silos by deeply integrating with design tools (Figma, Adobe), project management (Notion, Linear), and marketing platforms (HubSpot), creating a complete digital workflow." }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "tag": "h2",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "Looking Ahead" }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              { "type": "text", "text": "The future of digital asset management belongs to platforms that seamlessly blend AI capabilities, collaborative experiences, and ecosystem integration. MuseDAM continues to explore and innovate on this path." }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "version": 1
      }
    }
